{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"512","heading":"Forfeiture of certain motor vehicles and motor vehicle parts","label":"512 Forfeiture of certain motor vehicles and motor vehicle parts","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/ptI/ch25","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs512","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Amendments1994—Subsec. (a)(2)(A). substituted “chapter 301 title 49” for “the National Traffic and Motor Vehicle Safety Act of 1966”.Pub. L. 103–272"],"amendments":["Amendments1994—Subsec. (a)(2)(A). substituted “chapter 301 title 49” for “the National Traffic and Motor Vehicle Safety Act of 1966”.Pub. L. 103–272"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":null,"label":"a","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs512%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs512%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"in the case of a motor vehicle part, such part is attached to a motor vehicle and the owner of such motor vehicle does not know that the identification number has been removed, obliterated, tampered with, or altered;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs512%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/a/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs512%2Fa%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is authorized by the Secretary of Transportation under chapter 301 of title 49; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/a/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs512%2Fa%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"conforms to applicable State law;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs512%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"such removal, obliteration, tampering, or alteration is caused by collision or fire or is carried out as described in ; orsection 511(b) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/a/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs512%2Fa%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"such motor vehicle or part is in the possession or control of a motor vehicle scrap processor who does not know that such identification number was removed, obliterated, tampered with, or altered in any manner other than by collision or fire or as described in .section 511(b) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":null,"label":"b","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs512%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs512%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the seizure and condemnation of vessels, vehicles, merchandise, and baggage for violation of customs laws, and procedures for summary and judicial forfeiture applicable to such violations;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs512%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the disposition of such vessels, vehicles, merchandise, and baggage or the proceeds from such disposition;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs512%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the remission or mitigation of such forfeiture; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs512%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the compromise of claims and the award of compensation to informers with respect to such forfeiture;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":null,"label":"c","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s512","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs512%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"As used in this section, the terms “identification number”, “motor vehicle”, and “motor vehicle scrap processor” have the meanings given those terms in .section 511 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
